Please just say yes.
Please.

17:42.230 --> 17:44.163
[ Inhales shakily ]

17:48.703 --> 17:50.236
I love you.

17:50.238 --> 17:54.840
♪♪

17:55.509 --> 17:57.175
Deran: You got to tell me
how this guy has

17:57.177 --> 17:58.777
all these cars
ready to go for us.

17:58.779 --> 18:00.913
Well, Herman doesn't do
much business, man.

18:00.915 --> 18:02.180
[ Engine starts ]

18:02.182 --> 18:04.450
Although, he's got a few
theories on why that is.

18:04.452 --> 18:06.318
Why, 'cause he's out
in the middle of nowhere?

18:06.320 --> 18:07.653
No.

18:07.655 --> 18:09.722
Blames Jiffy Lube for doing
cheap oil changes

18:09.724 --> 18:11.724
on utility fleets.

18:11.726 --> 18:14.192
Thinks that they stole
his business.

18:14.194 --> 18:15.193
So?

18:15.195 --> 18:18.464
So, one day,
he had an idea.

18:18.466 --> 18:22.000
If a business is doing thousands
of oil changes on fleet cars

18:22.002 --> 18:24.737
that look exactly alike,

18:24.739 --> 18:27.005
maybe no one's gonna miss
a few here or there.

18:27.007 --> 18:28.741
I don't know, man.
That's pretty sketchy,

18:28.743 --> 18:31.677
getting pulled over
at the border in a bunch
of stolen cars, no?

18:31.679 --> 18:35.281
Yeah, man, well, then,
we'll just switch the plates
out like we always do.

18:35.283 --> 18:40.686
Plus, you got 8,000 cars
a day that go through Calexico,

18:40.688 --> 18:42.688
70,000 through San Ysidro.

18:42.690 --> 18:46.559
So, we just wait 'til rush hour
a couple days after we nab Pope,

18:46.561 --> 18:48.360
the heat'll be off us,

18:48.362 --> 18:50.229
and they'll just wave us
right on through.

18:50.231 --> 18:52.498
I don't think you realize
how much heat we're gonna
have on us.

18:52.500 --> 18:54.366
Yeah, it's only gonna be
for a day or two, man.

18:54.368 --> 18:56.969
They're gonna put our faces
on some poster.

18:56.971 --> 18:59.638
And federal dragnet manpower
is expensive, man.

18:59.640 --> 19:02.641
[ Engine starts ]

19:02.643 --> 19:05.378
Alright.
I'm doing number three.

19:08.649 --> 19:10.049
Alright.

19:12.720 --> 19:14.987
Yeah, seems alright.

19:14.989 --> 19:17.723
We should take them for
a test drive before we go.

19:17.725 --> 19:24.530
♪♪

19:24.532 --> 19:31.203
♪♪

19:31.205 --> 19:35.407
♪ Oh, baby, gotta
put me back together ♪

19:35.409 --> 19:39.678
♪ I need your smooth dog lovin',
oh, yeah ♪

19:39.680 --> 19:43.615
♪ And so I'm sending in
the little monster ♪

19:43.617 --> 19:46.752
♪ Gonna turn it up
inside your head ♪

19:46.754 --> 19:48.620
[ Music stops ]
Jesus, Smurf.

19:48.622 --> 19:51.157
What's the matter,
baby?

19:51.159 --> 19:54.560
You getting tired of women
showing up unannounced?

19:54.562 --> 19:57.095
[ Chuckles ]

19:57.097 --> 19:59.899
How are you liking
the house?

20:01.502 --> 20:05.437
It's great.
Yeah?

20:05.439 --> 20:07.874
Yeah.
You wanna keep it?

20:09.844 --> 20:11.243
Yeah.

20:11.245 --> 20:14.580
How much
is she giving you?

20:14.582 --> 20:17.916
What are you
talking about?

20:17.918 --> 20:20.853
Julia's skimming.
[ Scoffs ]

20:26.995 --> 20:29.928
Are you taking a piece?

20:29.930 --> 20:31.597
What?

20:31.599 --> 20:33.032
No.

20:36.537 --> 20:38.204
I-I swear.

20:38.206 --> 20:44.343
♪♪

20:44.345 --> 20:45.811
Mm.

20:45.813 --> 20:47.480
She's gone.

20:50.218 --> 20:52.018
Uh...what?

20:52.020 --> 20:55.554
She's not welcome
in my house anymore.

20:55.556 --> 21:00.559
♪♪

21:00.561 --> 21:03.495
O-Okay.

21:03.497 --> 21:07.366
She's not welcome<i> here</i>
anymore.

21:07.368 --> 21:08.701
Ever.

21:08.703 --> 21:13.439
♪♪

21:13.441 --> 21:16.909
Beautiful boy.

21:16.911 --> 21:18.911
Beautiful.

21:22.116 --> 21:23.782
Come here, baby.

21:23.784 --> 21:30.456
♪♪

21:30.458 --> 21:32.791
We clear?

21:32.793 --> 21:33.992
Yeah.

21:33.994 --> 21:41.934
♪♪

21:41.936 --> 21:49.808
♪♪

21:49.810 --> 21:51.143
Did the safe house
check out?

21:51.145 --> 21:53.079
Yeah.
Guns are stashed.

21:53.081 --> 21:54.947
Cars are all gassed up
and ready to go.

21:54.949 --> 21:56.749
I'll send you a pin
with the location.

21:56.751 --> 21:59.285
Alright.
And what else is out there?

21:59.287 --> 22:01.754
Nothing.
Just buzzards and dirt.

22:01.756 --> 22:03.889
We hit it
on the state road here.

22:03.891 --> 22:05.624
This is just
20 miles of nothing.

22:05.626 --> 22:07.293
And then we hit it from the side
on one of these

22:07.295 --> 22:11.297
utility access roads,
and then we head out this way.

22:11.299 --> 22:13.099
That's where
the safe house is.

22:13.101 --> 22:14.633
I mean,
this is all desert.

22:14.635 --> 22:17.569
Just a bunch of trails, maybe a
few fire roads if we're lucky.

22:17.571 --> 22:20.038
We should assume that
the transport deputies

22:20.040 --> 22:21.507
are gonna get a call out.

22:21.509 --> 22:23.842
Police will respond
in force.

22:23.844 --> 22:25.444
Helicopters, too,
probably.

22:25.446 --> 22:27.780
Yeah, so we'll be using
dirt bikes and dune buggies.

22:27.782 --> 22:29.181
We'll be out
of there fast.

22:29.183 --> 22:30.983
They'll assume we're taking
the state road,

22:30.985 --> 22:32.518
and we'll be out
in the open desert.

22:32.520 --> 22:34.186
Can Billy's guy definitely
get us the information

22:34.188 --> 22:35.521
on the transport bus?

22:35.523 --> 22:37.523
Which one Pope's gonna be on
and when?

22:37.525 --> 22:39.926
Yeah.
That's what he says.

22:39.928 --> 22:42.060
You got any more
of those GSM chips?

22:42.062 --> 22:44.196
The Israeli ones?
Yeah. Why?

22:44.198 --> 22:46.598
I can slip one to Pope
when I see him.

22:46.600 --> 22:49.735
We can pinpoint him
within about two feet.

22:49.737 --> 22:52.538
I mean, they're gonna do
a full body cavity search
when they move him,

22:52.540 --> 22:54.606
so I don't think
that's a good idea.

22:54.608 --> 22:55.607
He'll figure it out.

22:55.609 --> 22:57.276
No, I-I-I trust
Billy's guy

22:57.278 --> 22:58.611
to come through with
the right information.

22:58.613 --> 23:01.079
I don't think we need
to go and GPS Pope.

23:01.081 --> 23:03.950
Hey, man, he's right.

23:03.952 --> 23:06.084
It's a good idea.

23:06.086 --> 23:15.427
♪♪

23:15.429 --> 23:18.965
Just thought you might
be hungry, baby.

23:18.967 --> 23:20.466
Not really.

23:23.638 --> 23:26.038
Come on, baby.

23:26.040 --> 23:29.175
You're a growing boy.

23:29.177 --> 23:32.245
[ Smooching ]

23:34.382 --> 23:37.049
Come on.

23:37.051 --> 23:39.718
What's gonna happen
to Julia?

23:39.720 --> 23:40.719
That's up to her.

23:40.721 --> 23:43.189
You're really not gonna
let her come back?

23:43.191 --> 23:46.525
Families have to have
trust, baby.

23:46.527 --> 23:48.661
Without trust,
anything can happen.

23:48.663 --> 23:51.497
[ Telephone ringing ]

23:56.070 --> 23:58.070
You're not gonna
answer that?

23:58.072 --> 23:59.805
I'm sure
it's nobody important.

23:59.807 --> 24:02.675
[ Ringing continues ]

24:02.677 --> 24:04.142
[ Line ringing ]

24:04.144 --> 24:06.879
Come on, Andrew.
Pick up, pick up.

24:06.881 --> 24:08.881
Please pick up.

24:08.883 --> 24:18.891
♪♪

24:18.893 --> 24:20.827
[ Receiver clicks ]

24:20.829 --> 24:26.765
♪♪

24:26.767 --> 24:29.435
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:34.442 --> 24:36.642
Hey.

24:36.644 --> 24:38.711
I brought some photos
for you.

24:38.713 --> 24:41.247
Hold it right there.

24:41.249 --> 24:44.584
The, uh, guard at the gate
said they were okay.

24:48.122 --> 24:49.521
Okay.

24:49.523 --> 24:50.623
Thanks.

24:53.127 --> 24:55.861
How you doing, man?

24:55.863 --> 24:57.996
I'm okay.

24:57.998 --> 25:04.871
♪♪

25:04.873 --> 25:07.139
DA agreed to a deal.

25:07.141 --> 25:10.208
[ Breathes deeply ]
Okay.

25:10.210 --> 25:12.478
So, you're being
transferred?

25:12.480 --> 25:14.613
Yeah.
Good.

25:14.615 --> 25:15.814
When?

25:15.816 --> 25:18.216
Soon.

25:18.218 --> 25:20.218
How's the rest
of the family?

25:20.220 --> 25:21.420
Hanging in there.

25:21.422 --> 25:23.556
Craig and Deran found
a new spot.

25:23.558 --> 25:24.623
It's nice.

25:24.625 --> 25:26.959
It's gonna have
everything they need.

25:26.961 --> 25:28.294
Right.

25:28.296 --> 25:30.429
I've never seen
these before.

25:30.431 --> 25:32.999
There's a good one in there
of you and my mom.

25:34.368 --> 25:36.302
That's the one.

25:36.304 --> 25:38.170
Look on the back.

25:38.172 --> 25:43.909
♪♪

25:43.911 --> 25:49.515
♪♪

25:49.517 --> 25:53.019
So, you're gonna
keep us posted, okay?

25:55.255 --> 25:57.189
Yeah.

25:57.191 --> 26:00.392
Stay safe, man.

26:00.394 --> 26:02.194
We're done here.

26:02.196 --> 26:08.400
♪♪

26:08.402 --> 26:10.869
Can I keep one
of those pictures?

26:10.871 --> 26:12.738
The one of me and Julia.

26:16.544 --> 26:18.311
It's fine.

26:22.082 --> 26:23.816
See you soon.

26:23.818 --> 26:29.121
♪♪

26:31.492 --> 26:34.493
♪ Ah, whoo! ♪

26:34.495 --> 26:37.496
♪♪

26:37.498 --> 26:39.098
♪ Ah, whoo! ♪

26:39.100 --> 26:41.901
♪ Just keep your eye
on the street ♪

26:41.903 --> 26:44.636
♪ Gas under the feet ♪

26:44.638 --> 26:49.108
♪ Let's see if we get very far ♪

26:51.178 --> 26:54.513
♪ Ah, whoo! ♪

26:54.515 --> 26:57.517
♪ Getaway, getaway, getaway ♪

26:57.519 --> 26:58.984
♪ Whoo! ♪

26:58.986 --> 27:03.322
♪♪

27:03.324 --> 27:07.859
You didn't catch shit, man.
What's going on?

27:07.861 --> 27:09.529
I'm going to Indo.

27:09.531 --> 27:11.997
I won't be missing out
on any waves.

27:11.999 --> 27:14.600
Yeah.

27:14.602 --> 27:18.003
You gonna call him?

27:18.005 --> 27:19.471
Who?

27:19.473 --> 27:21.873
You know who.

27:21.875 --> 27:24.476
I don't know.
I doubt he'd want to see me.

27:24.478 --> 27:25.945
So?

27:25.947 --> 27:28.080
What do<i> you</i> want?

27:31.485 --> 27:33.885
I don't know.

27:33.887 --> 27:36.288
The happiest
I ever saw you

27:36.290 --> 27:38.558
was when you and Adrian
moved in together.

27:38.560 --> 27:40.426
You should find him.

27:40.428 --> 27:46.232
♪♪

27:46.234 --> 27:52.237
♪♪

27:52.239 --> 27:54.740
[ Knocking ]

28:04.452 --> 28:05.651
♪ Head like a hole ♪

28:05.653 --> 28:06.986
Can I come in?

28:06.988 --> 28:08.988
♪ Black as your soul ♪

28:08.990 --> 28:14.594
♪ I'd rather die
than give you control ♪

28:14.596 --> 28:19.064
♪ Bow down before
the one you serve ♪

28:19.066 --> 28:22.868
♪ You're going to get
what you deserve ♪

28:22.870 --> 28:28.073
♪ Bow down before
the one you serve ♪

28:28.075 --> 28:30.676
You want
something to drink?

28:30.678 --> 28:33.745
I got Cokes, beer.

28:33.747 --> 28:36.015
Uh, yeah,
beer would be good.

28:36.017 --> 28:41.420
♪♪

28:41.422 --> 28:46.826
♪♪

28:46.828 --> 28:50.362
♪ God money's not looking
for the cure ♪

28:50.364 --> 28:52.965
Your lip looks better.

28:52.967 --> 28:54.766
Hm!

28:54.768 --> 28:56.836
Yeah, you got hands.
I'll give you that.

28:56.838 --> 28:59.171
♪ On the backs of the bruised ♪

28:59.173 --> 29:01.641
♪ God money's not one
to choose ♪

29:01.643 --> 29:04.043
Smurf kicked me out.

29:04.045 --> 29:07.379
She took my car keys,
my money, all of it.

29:07.381 --> 29:11.651
I don't even have my clothes,
and they're my clothes!

29:11.653 --> 29:13.785
I swear to God,
she's a psycho, Baz.

29:13.787 --> 29:15.187
I-I mean, we all knew
she was crazy,

29:15.189 --> 29:17.323
but you should have
seen her.

29:17.325 --> 29:19.791
And Andrew, he -- he -- he -- he
didn't even do shit.

29:19.793 --> 29:21.260
He didn't even try to help.
I --

29:21.262 --> 29:22.995
He's scared, Jules.
No shit!

29:22.997 --> 29:26.465
I'm scared, too!

29:26.467 --> 29:30.602
[ Sighs, sniffs ]

29:30.604 --> 29:32.204
I need to crash here
for a bit.

29:32.206 --> 29:34.806
Just -- Just while
I figure shit out.

29:34.808 --> 29:36.808
No, Julia...

29:36.810 --> 29:38.810
I know,
it's over between us.

29:38.812 --> 29:40.145
But I won't interfere
with your shit.

29:40.147 --> 29:42.481
No. No. No.
What?

29:42.483 --> 29:45.617
♪ You're going to get
what you deserve ♪

29:45.619 --> 29:47.887
You can't stay here.

29:47.889 --> 29:50.890
Why?

29:50.892 --> 29:53.425
Smurf came by.
I'm sorry.

29:53.427 --> 29:55.495
You're sorry?

29:55.497 --> 29:56.828
Seriously?

29:56.830 --> 29:58.297
Look,
if she kicked you out,

29:58.299 --> 30:01.701
imagine what
she's gonna do to me.

30:01.703 --> 30:05.104
Baz, I don't have
anywhere else to go.

30:05.106 --> 30:07.707
You gotta leave, Julia.

30:07.709 --> 30:09.308
Baz.

30:09.310 --> 30:11.377
Look, you brought this
on yourself.

30:11.379 --> 30:12.778
You stole from her.
I mean --

30:12.780 --> 30:14.580
No, I was trying
to help Pope.

30:14.582 --> 30:16.983
No, you were trying
to help you.

30:19.453 --> 30:21.387
Andrew -- he can't -- he can't
stay there with her.

30:21.389 --> 30:23.723
She's making him worse,
and she likes him like that.

30:23.725 --> 30:26.125
You know that.

30:26.127 --> 30:29.328
Look, I can
look after Pope.

30:29.330 --> 30:30.396
You got to go now.

30:30.398 --> 30:34.333
Please, please, please,
don't do this.

30:34.335 --> 30:36.435
I need you.
I need you.

30:37.871 --> 30:39.539
I need you.

30:39.541 --> 30:44.876
♪♪

30:44.878 --> 30:47.747
Take some cash, okay?

30:47.749 --> 30:50.215
Oh, you piece of shit.
No, take it.

30:50.217 --> 30:53.819
Get off.

30:53.821 --> 30:57.889
You worthless
piece of shit.

30:57.891 --> 31:00.226
I loved you.

31:00.228 --> 31:06.298
♪♪

31:06.300 --> 31:08.901
Come on. Point with a nice
southwest swell.

31:08.903 --> 31:10.702
You're not gonna
miss that shit?

31:10.704 --> 31:14.039
Bro, I have been surfing that
point since I was in diapers.

31:14.041 --> 31:17.009
I'm looking forward
to surfing new shit, man.

31:23.785 --> 31:25.918
You guys see
who did this?

31:26.988 --> 31:29.521
Nah, man.
Sucks, huh?

31:29.523 --> 31:32.191
Yeah.

31:32.193 --> 31:34.059
Yeah, that shit's gonna be
hard to get off.

31:34.061 --> 31:35.727
I'm sure you got something
to take it off.

31:35.729 --> 31:38.397
Back where you live?
La Jolla, am I right?

31:43.404 --> 31:45.270
You guys were
on the lineup, yeah?

31:45.272 --> 31:46.472
I was.
Caught a few good ones

31:46.474 --> 31:48.073
until Chewbacca over here
snaked me.

31:48.075 --> 31:51.477
[ Rock music plays ]

31:51.479 --> 31:53.879
[ Grunting ]

31:53.881 --> 32:03.555
♪♪

32:03.557 --> 32:12.898
♪♪

32:12.900 --> 32:22.574
♪♪

32:22.576 --> 32:32.318
♪♪

32:32.320 --> 32:33.486
Ah.

32:36.524 --> 32:40.059
Now, that's the shit
I<i> am</i> gonna miss.

32:40.061 --> 32:41.593
Yeah, me too.

32:41.595 --> 32:43.462
[ Engine starts ]

32:50.204 --> 32:52.338
Hey.

32:52.340 --> 32:53.472
Hey.

32:53.474 --> 32:56.075
Al Carbon,
extra avocado.

32:56.077 --> 32:58.810
Thank you.
You're welcome.

32:58.812 --> 33:02.548
I missed you.

33:02.550 --> 33:03.549
I'm at work. Stop

33:03.551 --> 33:05.484
What are they gonna do?
Fire you?

33:05.486 --> 33:07.553
[ Laughs ]

33:07.555 --> 33:09.955
I thought we were gonna go
to Sal's for lunch.

33:09.957 --> 33:13.959
I can't -- I've got to go
to the bowling alley and
show the new owners around.

33:13.961 --> 33:16.696
There is something
I need your help with
before we can go.

33:16.698 --> 33:20.366
It's the, uh -- it's just
an update to the trust document.

33:20.368 --> 33:22.702
There's a new file
on there.

33:22.704 --> 33:24.303
It's no big deal.

33:24.305 --> 33:26.972
I just changed one thing
on one page of each of them.

33:26.974 --> 33:28.374
What?

33:28.376 --> 33:30.976
It's the sentence that
gave me temporary authority

33:30.978 --> 33:33.379
over my uncles' money.

33:33.381 --> 33:35.548
I changed it
to permanent authority.

33:37.785 --> 33:40.219
It's a notarized
document, J.

33:42.590 --> 33:47.326
I can't just change the trusts
without their approval.

33:47.328 --> 33:51.997
That's illegal.
I could -- I could go to jail.

33:51.999 --> 33:57.669
♪♪

33:57.671 --> 34:03.275
♪♪

34:03.277 --> 34:07.613
My uncles are extremely
dangerous people.

34:07.615 --> 34:10.216
They're criminals.
Pope is a murderer.

34:10.218 --> 34:12.084
You -- You know
about that.

34:12.086 --> 34:14.019
All three of them are.

34:14.021 --> 34:15.555
Craig and Deran?

34:18.292 --> 34:22.094
It's why
we have to leave.

34:22.096 --> 34:24.830
They want
to murder me, too.

34:24.832 --> 34:27.299
I'm just a loose end.

34:27.301 --> 34:29.902
And they are gonna want
all the money for themselves.

34:29.904 --> 34:34.774
♪♪

34:34.776 --> 34:36.908
[ Crying ]

34:36.910 --> 34:41.847
♪♪

34:41.849 --> 34:43.983
Hey.

34:43.985 --> 34:45.184
I'm not interested.

34:45.186 --> 34:48.988
You're Julia, right?

34:48.990 --> 34:51.991
I'm Thorpe.
Remember?

34:51.993 --> 34:53.859
Thorpe? Uh...

34:53.861 --> 34:56.261
I'm a friend of Baz's.

34:56.263 --> 34:58.631
I've been at your house.

35:01.669 --> 35:03.935
Is everything cool?

35:03.937 --> 35:07.072
You seem kind of upset.

35:07.074 --> 35:09.208
No, actually.

35:09.210 --> 35:11.477
Nothing is cool
right now.

35:11.479 --> 35:14.614
I got something might help you
feel better.

35:17.485 --> 35:19.284
Um, no.

35:19.286 --> 35:21.753
But thank you.

35:21.755 --> 35:24.156
I get it. It's cool.

35:24.158 --> 35:27.026
It's just not my thing.
Hey, no worries.

35:27.028 --> 35:29.228
But hey, my place is
just up the beach.

35:29.230 --> 35:31.631
A couple people are hanging out
you might know.

35:31.633 --> 35:33.432
Get off the street
before it gets cold.

35:33.434 --> 35:36.101
Thinking of
ordering a pizza.

35:36.103 --> 35:45.777
♪♪

35:45.779 --> 35:47.313
Shit.

35:47.315 --> 35:48.980
Hey!

35:48.982 --> 35:50.182
Wait.

35:50.184 --> 35:57.390
♪♪

35:59.994 --> 36:09.068
♪♪

